        ]
      ],
      [
        "This house was the birthplace and childhood home of great operatic tenor Antonio Paoli ( 1871-1946 ) until 1883 . It was in Ponce 's rich cultural environment that Paoli was first exposed to the arts , and this house is the only property remaining in Puerto Rico associated with the island 's first performing artist of international renown",
        [
          "/wiki/Opera",
          "/wiki/Tenor",
          "/wiki/Antonio_Paoli"
